text.section:
If a Natural Resources police officer apprehends a person for violating any law punishable as a misdemeanor, the officer may prepare a written or electronic citation containing:
A notice to appear in court;
The name and address of the person charged;
Relevant license numbers, if any;
The offense charged;
The time and place the person shall appear in court;
An acknowledgment of receipt of the citation by the person charged made in a manner determined by the Department; and
Other pertinent information required by the Secretary.
